    • assignTemporaryRowNumbersToNewRows

      protected long assignTemporaryRowNumbersToNewRows(long tempRowNum, int rowNumColumn)
      Assign row numbers to newly added table rows. Some tables use row numbers, when building the table updates used to generate the SQL commands to adjust the database, to match up a row that has had one or more column values or its position in the table changed with the same row prior to the change(s). New rows are initialized with a blank row number (the row number is assigned when the table is written to the database). If a subsequent table store operation is performed then rows with blank row numbers can't be matched, so assigning a temporary row number allows matching.
      Parameters:
      tempRowNum - Starting number for the temporary row number. This should be negative so as not to duplicate an actual row numbers in another table row
      rowNumColumn - Table column containing the row number, model coordinates
      Returns:
      The updated temporary row number value

    • pasteData

      protected boolean pasteData(Object[] cellData, int numColumns, boolean isInsert, boolean isAddIfNeeded, boolean isStartFirstColumn, boolean isCombineAsSingleEdit, boolean isHighlightPastedData, boolean isNumHiddenRowsCanChange, boolean isReplaceAllExisting, boolean isForceOverwrite)
      Paste the contents of the supplied cell data array into the table. Depending on the input flag values, current rows are either overwritten, excess rows are discarded, or new rows are inserted below the currently selected row to contain the pasted data. The currently selected column determines the column alignment for the pasted data. Pasted column data beyond the table boundaries are discarded
      Parameters:
      cellData - Array of cell values to be inserted
      numColumns - Number of columns represented by the cell data array
      isInsert - True to add new rows to contain the pasted data; false to overwrite existing cells in the paste range and only add rows if needed
      isAddIfNeeded - True to add new rows if the pasted data doesn't fit; false to discard excess rows
      isStartFirstColumn - True if pasting of the data begins in the first column; false to begin pasting at the currently cell with the focus
      isCombineAsSingleEdit - True to combine the pasted data as a single edit; false to not alter the undo manager's handling of the edit sequence (this allows handling externally so that other edits may be grouped with the paste operation)
      isHighlightPastedData - True to highlight the cells containing the pasted data
      isNumHiddenRowsCanChange - True if the number of rows can change based on the pasted data (e.g., when pasting an array definition into a structure table)
      isReplaceAllExisting - True to replace all of the existing data in the table
      isForceOverwrite - True to overwrite cells, even if considered unalterable. This is only used when importing tables
      Returns:
      True if the user elected to cancel pasting the data following a cell validation error

      Reset the table header renderer and the mouse listener for column resizing (via mouse button double click) following a change to the look and feel

    • printTable

      protected void printTable(String tableName, List<CcddClassesDataTable.FieldInformation> fieldInformation, Component parent, int orientation)
      Output the table to the user-selected printer (or file)
      Parameters:
      tableName - Table name; displayed at the top of each printed page
      fieldInformation - Data field information for the fields associated with this table; null if no data fields are associated with the table
      parent - Parent window for this table
      orientation - Page orientation; e.g., PageFormat.LANDSCAPE or PageFormat.PORTRAIT
